> hmmm getting similar issue. I'm using podman on macos, not sure what I do `allow_other` or where to execute. It would be great if someone can give more hint. Thanks

@kkharji  
When you're calling to mount the FUSE filesystem, you need to make sure to add the extra mount option `allow_other` to the mount command.  How you do that depends on the particulars of your system type and how you mounted the FUSE filesystem.
